subSubSection.paragraph:
Differential diagnosis — The new species is most similar to
Adactylidium ficorum Goldarazena and Ochoa, 2001
, described from Puerto Rico and Egypt (
Goldarazena et al. 2001
) in having three setae on genu I, one seta on genu III, and well developed appo. The new species differs from
A. ficorum
in having apsej not fused with appr (apsej fused with appr in
A. ficorum
), setae 1 b completely absent (alveoli of setae 1 b present in
A. ficorum
) and median projections present on apgn (absent in
A. ficorum
).
